 <h2>Data Collection</h2>
 <h3>What Data Do We Collect?</h3>
 <p>The General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) defines personal data as any information that can identify a person directly or indirectly. This includes not just obvious details like your name, but also more discrete information like electronic location data and other online identifiers.</p>
 <p><strong>Direct Information You Provide:</strong> When you engage with us, such as by purchasing, subscribing to our newsletter, reviewing our products, or interacting on social media, we might collect:</p>
 <ul>
 <li><strong>Name</strong></li>
 <li><strong>Email</strong></li>
 <li><strong>Mobile number</strong></li>
 <li><strong>Address</strong></li>
 <li><strong>Transactional and payment information</strong></li>
 <li><strong>Content you submit:</strong> This can be in the form of product reviews, posts, or any other information you choose to provide.</li>
 </ul>
 <p><strong>Device and Usage Information:</strong> When you visit our website, we gather details related to:</p>
 <ul>
 <li><strong>Device and network:</strong> Information about the device you're using, your network, and browser type.</li>
 <li><strong>Activity:</strong> This includes your actions on our site and the version of the app you might be using.</li>
 <li><strong>Cookies and Tracking:</strong> These technologies offer insights that allow us to enhance your experience on our website by understanding site usage patterns and the effectiveness of our emails.</li>
 </ul>
 <p><strong>Third-party Information Collection:</strong> We also receive data about you from external sources like:</p>
 <ul>
 <li><strong>Advertising networks</strong></li>
 <li><strong>Data analytics providers</strong></li>
 <li><strong>Mailing list providers</strong></li>
 </ul>
 <p>This helps us tailor our services better to your needs and interests.</p>
 <h3>How We Collect Your Data</h3>
 <p>We gather information about you through various methods:</p>
 <ul>
 <li><strong>Direct Submission:</strong> This happens when you complete our registration form or provide personal information in another manner.</li>
 <li><strong>Website Interaction:</strong> Your actions and behavior on our website also contribute to the data we collect about you.</li>
 <li><strong>Public Sources:</strong> Occasionally, we might acquire information about you from publicly available sources.</li>
 </ul>
 <h3>How We Use Your Data</h3>
 <p>Under GDPR, we have to have a lawful reason to use your personal data. We use your information primarily to deliver our products and services, as well as enhance your experience with us. Here's a breakdown:</p>
 
 <ul>
 <li><strong>Account Management:</strong> Create and manage your account.</li>
 <li><strong>Service Delivery:</strong> Supply our products and services and improve our site and offerings.</li>
 <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Communicate about products, offers, news, and respond to emails or calls.</li>
 <li><strong>Site Enhancement:</strong> Debug to fix errors, personalize your site experience, and gauge email effectiveness.</li>
 <li><strong>Legal & Financial Compliance:</strong> Meet our obligations and enforce our terms and conditions.</li>
 <li>
 <strong>Specific Tasks:</strong>
 <ul>
 <li>Testimonials</li>
 <li>Process payments</li>
 <li>Provide support</li>
 <li>Admin tasks</li>
 <li>Manage orders</li>
 <li>Resolve disputes</li>
 </ul>
 </li>
 <li><strong>Marketing:</strong> If you've opted in or permitted by law, we might contact you with information, news, or offers. Rest assured, we respect your rights and never send spam. You can opt-out anytime.</li>
 </ul>

 <p><span style="font-style: italic;">Note:</span> The ads you see are often based on our data about you or your past interactions with our site.</p>
